FBIS3-33799 "drnes021_m_94002" FBIS-NES-94-021 Document Type:Daily Report 1 Feb 1994 JORDAN Al-Shar' Offers Condolences on Death of Diplomat JN3101192594 Amman Jordan Television Network in Arabic 1800 GMT 31 Jan 94 JN3101192594 Amman Jordan Television Network Language: Arabic Article Type:BFN [Text] The minister of state for foreign affairs received a condolence cable from Faruq al-Shar', foreign minister of the fraternal Syrian Arab Republic, on the martyrdom of Na'ib 'Umran al-Ma'ayitah, counselor to the Jordanian Embassy in Beirut. In his cable, al-Shar' said: I send to you my sincere condolences on the death of Na'ib 'Umran al-Ma'ayitah in a reprehensible crime. He added: I also offer my condolences to the al-Ma'ayitah family and ask God almighty to have mercy on the deceased and grant his family patience and comfort.
